quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  41,1,ῌā‘ mīm
  41,2,"Sent down from the Merciful, the Compassionate"
  41,3,"a Book of revelations well expounded, an Arabic Koran for those endowed with knowledge"
  41,4,"It proclaims joyful tidings and a warning: yet most of them turn their backs and hear not"
  41,5,"They say: ‘Our hearts are proof against that to which you call us. Our ears are stopped, and a veil stands between ourselves and you. Do as you will, and so will we.‘"
  41,6,"Say: ‘I am but a mortal like yourselves. It is revealed to me that your God is one God. Therefore take the straight path to Him and implore His forgiveness. Woe betide those who serve other gods besides Him"
  41,7,who give no alms and disbelieve in the life to come
  41,8,"As for those who have faith and do good works, an endless recompense awaits them.‘"